Archive: Great Britain's Lizzy Yarnold wins World Skeleton title
Great Britain's Lizzy Yarnold'swins the World Skeleton titleat the final event in Koeniggssee in Germany.The Briton only finished ninth in heat one, but it was enough to clinch the title by 152 points as the second heat was cancelled due to bad weather.Britain's Shelley Rudman finished third in the standings after securing bronze in Germany.Watch live coverage of the women's third round of the World Cup season from Altenberg, Germany on the BBC Sport website on Friday 9th January at 08:00 GMT.Available to UK users only.